<section class="xs-col-12 lg-col-9 pt1 mb4 pt2">
  <div class="mb2">
    <h2 class="mb1 bold">Slab Headings</h2>
    <p class="block">Caponi is BuzzFeed's slab typeface. It's default (and singular weight) is semibold. Caponi is intended to be used for News headlines only, and should never be smaller than an <code class="js-highlight">h5</code>, or 0.875 rem. An <code class="js-highlight">h6</code>, or anything classed with <code class="js-highlight">.type-6</code>, in combination with the <code class="js-highlight">.slab</code> class will default to Proxima. Headlines set in Caponi should be paired with body text set in Proxima.</p>
  </div>

